best hard threshold: T=20  norm_contingency=+0.716 (floor as-built T=12)
Read: if the SOFT sweep keeps norm_contingency near the hard value even at large tau,
the policy's soft boundary is NOT the bottleneck -- the plateau is elsewhere
(actuation/optimisation). If soft collapses it, sharpness IS the wall.
